<h2>Take a Tour of the Suda</h2>

<p>Is your hunger for classical knowledge <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=alpha%2C3230&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">insatiable</a>?
There's a lot in the Suda about Greek and Roman <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=science&amp;num_per_page=100">science</a>
and <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=medicine&amp;num_per_page=100">medicine</a>.
Did you know that <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=delta%2C448&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=50">Democritus</a>
was omniscient? Or that Akesias was a very bad name for a <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=alpha%2C842&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=50">proctologist</a>?
Curious what disease <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=Erasistratos&amp;field=hw_eng&amp;num_per_page=50">Erasistratos</a>
cured King Antiochus of? Or why <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?db=REAL&amp;search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;page_num=1&amp;searchstr=epsilon%2C1002&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=50">Empedokles</a>
surrounded Akragas with the skins of asses?
</p>
<p>
Ok, if you're not in a scientific mood, learn how Apollo prevented the oracles
of the <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=sigma%2C361&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">Chaldean
Sibyl</a> from being understood by <i>hoi polloi</i>. Read all about the
annoyingly just <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=alpha%2C3903&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">Aristides</a>,
Philoxenos <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=kappa%2C2647&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">the
tune-bender</a>, who was <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=alpha%2C2862&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">the
most courageous literary critic</a> in history, the captivating Ammonianus (<a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=alpha%2C1639&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">for
donkeys, at least</a>), and Chrysippus, <a
href="../sol-cgi-bin/search.cgi?search_method=QUERY&amp;login=guest&amp;enlogin=guest&amp;page_num=1&amp;user_list=LIST&amp;searchstr=chi%2C568&amp;field=adlerhw_gr&amp;num_per_page=25&amp;db=REAL">the
philosopher who left 'em laughing</a>.
</p>


